animal.description:
GAUGE!!
GOOD with dogs, GOOD with kids, UNKNOWN with cats

Adoption Fee: $450

Hello world!! My name is Gauge, and I am part of the construction trio that came to rescue. I came with my 2 brothers after we were found living in an abandoned house by some construction workers. No one is sure how long we were living there, but it is approximated by a vet that I am 10 months old, and I am all puppy! What does “all puppy” mean? I have been in rescue for a couple of weeks now, and I am learning everything about life, but I am going to need a patient person to love me while I learn. I have no manners, so you might need a hard hat to wear while you are teaching me about all the things that I need to learn so that you don’t hurt your head from the potential frustration that might come with this. Now, don’t get me wrong, because I am truly amazing, have the sweetest personality, absolutely LOVE people, and I love to play, but there is a lot that I am working on. These are the things that I am working on. I am still potty training, so I need a strict routine that will make sure that I continue learning how to go outside when I need to go. I will go in my kennel when I need to, but I am not a fan of it. I eventually settle down in there, but I want to be there the action is, so we’ve learned that being in my kennel in view of my family is what makes me settle faster. As you might imagine, I have had to learn to find food my entire young life, and so food for me is a great motivator, but it also means that I am very protective of my food because I am still learning that it will always be there, so for now, it is best that I am fed separately from any other dogs that might be in my new home. Due to food being a high value possession for me, bones and treats are something that I only get while in my kennel. It’s being used in a 2-fold manner in the sense that it’s making me realize that my kennel is a great place to be, but it’s also not creating a potential issue if there are other dogs in the home. Did I mention that I love to play? Oh boy! I have energy and love to run and play with my toys and people. I am not aggressive at all, but I am still learning when play time is over or when I need to settle because I am getting a little too excited. I currently live with my foster sister, and I do great with her even though she doesn’t always want me to play, so I am learning how to take correction. Well, there’s where I am in this great big world. I am learning so much, but I still have a ways to go. I know that I am cute and cuddly looking, but I want make sure that you know I am a work in progress. I will get there, but it will take some time, some love, and a whole lot of patience. Up for the challenge?? If so, head on over and fill out my application, and let’s get this party started! Hard hat potentially required, Gauge. (UPDATED 12/09/20)

animal.description:
After 13 years, a child developed asthma and Casper had to leave the only home and family he has ever known.  However, he was in dire need of medical attention for his eyes.  Due to the lack of vet care, he is partially sight impaired.  The medications he is now on will keep him comfortable and stop him from going completely blind. 
He has an inoperable tumor on his spleen.  However, one would never know it. He loves going for walks, enjoys the company of smaller dogs and would be okay with older, respectful kids ages 11yrs. +.  
Due to his age and health condition, we are seeking a local foster or forever home as he may have weeks to months to live the best time of his life. 

If interested in fostering, please contact us at 845-986-2473.  We will cover all food and medical expenses for Casper.  

Our adoption policy is to process applications first and then set up individual appointments. 
You are welcome to download and complete our adoption application from our website at wvhumane.org.  You can either fax it to us at 845-987-8995 or scan and email it back to us. 
Once processed, we will contact you.
If you have any questions, you are welcome to speak with our adoption counselor, Kelly, who can be reached Monday through Friday between 12 and 3 at 845-986-2473.

?Hardy is probably around 10 years old. He is happy, healthy, and such a HAM! He seems to be a small boston/rat terrier type. More importantly, what a good guy at the vet and with everyone he meets! He came from a local animal control facility where we saw him and knew immediately we had to rescue him. Those eyes, that grey face, the love he has to share. We will never know his past but his future looks exciting. #spoiledpup
Hardy has some aging changes in his joints which causes him discomfort at times so he will need to be kept on joint support, pain management, and fish oil to maintain his good looks and great demeanor. 
?Hardy Heart Love, welcome to the world of RESCUE?

From his foster family  - We LOVE him, he loves to snuggle, he runs in the yard like a puppy, he is quiet, loving and just a great friend.  He loves his naps, his jogs, his food and his toys.  
He has no separation anxiety, no food aggression, knows  no stranger.

Nikon is a handsome male German Shepherd who is approx. 2 yr. old and is  extra-large. He is not overweight, just big and tall. Nikon was found as a stray wandering around a mountainous area alone. He is strong physically and he is strong-willed.  Nikon will need a more advanced owner/handler, someone who is a strong pack leader and can set boundaries for him. We have started working with him on some basic commands but Nikon will definitely need obedience training. He is friendly to people and he’s fine with female dogs but no male dogs. animal.description:
Mina has been diagnosed with end-stage renal disease. She is expected to have between a year and two years to live. We hope to find Mina a family who will fill the time she has left with love and happiness. She will be in our hospice program; she can go to an adoptive home, but her necessary medical expenses will be covered by NMDR. Mina is also heartworm positive and is undergoing treatment. She needs to stay calm.

The NMDR Rehab Team is working with Mina to help her work through some behavior challenges. She needs a family who will be extra patient with her, and who preferably has previous experience with dogs. The NMDR Behavior Manager will talk to prospective adopters to explain the work we've done with her, and what will be the best home situation for her. 

To submit an application to adopt Mina, visit https://nmdr.org/our-dogs/adopt/

Fun Facts about Mina:
Friendly with people
Likes other dogs
Does great on leash
Social butterfly
Enjoys attention
Likes to play tug
Loves belly rubs and snuggling

Challenges for Mina:
Mina has some ear issues that we are treating 
While she loves other dogs, her dog play manners are a little rough. If she goes to a home with other dogs, they need be young, healthy, large and very tolerant.
She can play a little rough with her human friends, too.

To submit an application to adopt Mina, visit https://nmdr.org/our-dogs/adopt/

animal.description:
Minka was rescued from being euthanized at a shelter.  Her owners didn't want her after she had been found hit by a car ans usable to use her backlegs.  However when we met Minka we just knew that this girl had a lot of life left in her.  Her name, Minka, means strong willed warrior.

Minka is a 6 year old beagle.  In true Beagle style, Minka loves to run around the yard trying to get the scent of whatever critter may have run by.  Minka also loves being part of a pack.  She would do best in a house with other dogs.  
Minka's disability has never slowed her down. She is incredibly active.  She is fostered on a home that has an acre of land and Minka runs every inch of it.  She plays with a 65 lb dogs, runs around the yard with puppies and wrestles with pitbulls.  Minka also loves to cuddle with the small dogs.  She does howl at cats, but overall does well with them.

Minka does have potty accidents, mostly because she can't go outside whenever she needs to use the bathroom.  Diapers don't typically stay on her, and we use a lot of washable pads with her.  She weighs around 25 lbs and is good about being picked up and carried.  

Minka does try to stand and she can move her legs.  She just doesn't have strength.  We have tried hydrotherapy and exercises, and although she has improved a lot, we think she will need a chair for the rest of her life.

We know it will take a special family to want to adopt a special needs dog.  Minka deserves to find a loving forever home and we just know her perfect family is out there.

animal.breeds_label: Border Collie & Pit Bull Terrier Mix
animal.description:
Simba, border collie / pitbul mix, 2 yo, 52 lb male, neutered

Simba is very beatiful, graceful and gentle. He is attentive, smart and easy to have around. he can stare a hole in you with his bright bright eyes! He is a little shy at first but quickly warms up. He loves to come up and gently touch you with his lips as if checking if you want to pet him. He is great with our dogs at the sheleter, but might need some introduction with the new dogs. Needs a yard with 6' fence. He would be such an awesome loving and loyal companion to someone who wants a calmer dog.

Adoption fee $325 If interested please submit an adoption or foster application at http://sannicoladogrescue.com/ContactUs.aspx.

animal.breeds_label: Labrador Retriever & Australian Cattle Dog / Blue Heeler Mix
animal.description:
Jack, lab /red heeler mix, 52 lb, 2 yo, male, neutered

Jack is cuddly, friendly and makes the cutest faces when you talk to him. He wants to be loved and petted and puts his paws around you.

This wonderful dog had terrible past. He was said to be used as a bait dog and then he was abandoned at the pound. He was rescued on the last day from the EU list. You can see the scars on his face.

Jack need a safe loving home with no other pets and a 6' fence. No kids under 14 yo please. He loves to play and run as fast as he can. It is amazing to watch him enjoy his freedom for a change. This dog deserves a better life. Adoption fee $325 If interested please submit an adoption application at http://sannicoladogrescue.com/ContactUs.aspx.
